The evidence with the title 'What life was like in America 100 years ago - The Atlantic ' says Feb 11, 2016  ... Here is a closer look at America , one century ago. America suffered worse working conditions , in just about every way. For men: work for men was more widespread , more dangerous, worse paid, and, well, just more annoying. According to the 1920 census , 85 percent of men over 14 were in the labor force  ... 
